Package: cjapns
Type: Package
Title: Average Probability of Necessary and Sufficient Conditions in Conjoint
    Experiments
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("Lukas F.", "Stoetzer", email = "lukas.stoetzer@uni-wh.de",
           role = c("aut", "cre")),
    person("Asya", "Magazinnik", email = "a.magazinnik@hertie-school.org",
           role = "aut"))
Description: Implements the Average Probability of Necessary and Sufficient
    conditions (APNS) for measuring attribute relevance in conjoint
    experiments, as proposed by Stoetzer and Magazinnik (2026). Provides
    nonparametric estimation of the Expected Probability of Necessary and
    Sufficient conditions (EPNS) and Expected Average Probability of Necessary
    and Sufficient conditions (EAPNS) under separable monotonicity and
    conditional separable monotonicity assumptions. Supports multiple
    inference methods including parametric bootstrap, nonparametric bootstrap,
    jackknife, and analytical standard errors based on the folded normal
    approximation.
